Quilla Hugh "Porky" Freeman (June 29, 1916 in Vera Cruz, Missouri, United States – July 8, 2001) was an American Western swing performer, bandleader, and songwriter.
In the 1940s he led the Californian based band, the 'Porky Freeman Trio'.
